Open files and file descriptors are investigated using lsof and by examining /proc/$$/fd to understand Linux's file I/O management. Output and error redirection are tested using > and 2>&1, while piping operations are demonstrated using | and tee commands. System resource limits are checked with ulimit -a to identify constraints on file descriptors and processes. All technical observations and explanations of Linux I/O mechanisms are documented in IO_Investigation_Report.txt.
